Eve Southern https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eve_Southern 0 Eve Southern (August 23, 1900 – November 29, 1972) born Elva L. McDowell, was an American film actress. She appeared in 38 films between 1916 and 1936. She was chosen as one of Rolf Armstrong's sixteen screen beauties in 1930. She was buried in Valhalla Memorial Park Cemetery.
